


tril(1)                        Scilab Function                        tril(1)






NAME
  tril - lower triangular part of matrix

CALLING SEQUENCE
  tril(x [,k])

PARAMETERS

  x         : matrix

  k         : integer (default value 0)

DESCRIPTION
  Lower triangle part of a matrix.  tril(x,k)  is made by entries below the
  kth diagonal : k>0 (upper diagonal) and   k<0 (diagonals below the main
  diagonal).








































